Darkened Field
This larger field looks like it once was used to grow corn or possibly soybeans, but now it is covered in tall grass. An old Farmall tractor sits in the center of the field. Barely visible through the fog, you see the shadow of a farmhouse to the North, a decrepit barn to the East, and a treeline to the Northwest.

> northwest

> northwest

Treeline
This treeline is a row of pines that run along the western and northern edges of the field. Someone has built a deer blind here. Made of wood, it sits on stilts ten feet above the ground and is accessible by a ladder. You can go back Southeast to the field.

> Climb Ladder

> Climb Ladder

Old Deer Blind
This blind was constructed long ago; most of it is in shambles. A rusted folding chair sits at its center, a pile of hunting clothes lay tattered next to the chair, and an old Rusted Rifle leans against the wall. Looking down, you see large brown stains on the wooden floor

A ladder leads back down to the treeline.

> Take Rifle

> Take Rifle
You pick up the Rusted Rifle.
> Climb Ladder

> Climb Ladder

