Front Porch
You stand in front of an abandoned farmhouse. It is an old construction, possibly dating back to the '20s or '30s. The siding is greyed, and the paint has all but peeled away, suggesting that it has not been occupied for many years. On the porch; you see a broken porch swing, some empty planters, and a rocking chair.

The front door is directly North of you. You notice a second-story window just above the doorway.

> Use ladder

> Use ladder
You climb the ladder up and crawl through the broken window.
(You unlocked an Achievement.)

Upstairs Hallway East
You climb through the window and find yourself on a second floor hallway. Looking beside you next to the window, you find a letter on a small table. It reads:

Confession of Daniel Muir #1
(Letter has been logged into your Inventory. Type: READ LETTER to review.)

The hallway reveals that the interior of the house is in a state of blight. The wood floors are warped and buckled from exposure to the elements. The paint has peeled away from the walls, and parts of the ceiling have fallen in from water damage. You notice that a trail of fresh blood comes from down the hall and stops at a door directly in front of you to the North.

The hallway continues West, and there is a door next to you to the East.

> west

> west

Upstairs Hallway West
The narrow and warped second-floor hallway creaks and moans as you walk. The wind howls against the window behind you on the south wall, a cool draft passing through the single pane.

The hallway continues to the East, or you can take the Stairs to the first floor.

> use stairs

> use stairs

Living Room
Once the main dwelling space of this house, the living room is now a stale and dusty remnant of another age. There is a fireplace along the north wall, a gun rack resting just above it. A large wooden cabinet stands tall just a few feet to the right of the fireplace. A deer mount hangs on the east wall, staring into the room with faux eyes. There is a sofa in the center of the room facing the fireplace; a painting hangs on the wall behind it.

You can climb the stairs to the second floor, or travel South into the hallway.

> Use rifle

> Use rifle
You place the Rusted Rifle on the Gun Rack. You hear a loud clicking sound as if something has just unlocked.
(You unlocked an Achievement.)
