Bathroom
The bathroom is in shambles. The '70s mint green floor tile has all but broken apart and scattered into pieces. The sink is hanging off the wall, the mirror above the sink is shattered, and you seriously doubt that the grimy toilet and tub are in working order. There is a cupboard below the sink and a Laundry Shoot on the far wall.

> open cupboard

> open cupboard
You open it.
> take bottle

> take bottle
You pick it up.
Suddenly the door to the Bathroom SLAMS shut. Startled, you cautiously try the handle; it is locked.
> enter laundry shoot

> enter laundry shoot
It's a tight fit, but you manage to crawl into the laundry shoot and slowly slide down into the darkness below.
(You unlocked an Achievement.)

Cellar
You fall from the shoot into the cellar. You notice a piece of paper came out of the laundry shoot with you. It must have been stuck in there. It reads:

Confession of Daniel Muir #2
(Letter has been logged into your Inventory. Type: READ LETTER to review.)

The cellar is dreary and dank, with low ceilings, a dirt floor, and dust-ridden cobwebs sprawled along the log rafters. You can see a workbench against the wall nearest to you. Next to the bench is a metal cabinet. The Laundry Shoot you fell from earlier protrudes from the ceiling. There are stone steps in the corner of the room that lead upward.

You can see a Steps.
> Open cabinet

> Open cabinet
The old metal cabinet squeaks as you twist the knobs and swing the doors open.
> Take compound

> Take compound
You pick it up.
> take spare parts

> take spare parts
You pick it up.
> use steps

> use steps
You travel up the old stone steps and unlock the Cellar Doors.

Backyard
You walk outside onto a patio surrounded by tall grass. It is unnervingly quiet out here. In the grass, you can see a rusty swing set, and at the edge of the patio, there is a water spigot. On the side of the house, you spot cellar doors.

You can go South back into the house.

> south

> south

Kitchen
The kitchen is a mess.  You hear creaking and see that the back door has been left open, allowing dirt and dead leaves to collect on the floor. The kitchen table lay flipped and broken on its side, and the counter is covered in dishes and cooking utensils. Next to you is a dirty stove with a set of cupboards above it.

You can go back into the hallway South or exit North through the back door.

