Living Room
Once the main dwelling space of this house, the living room is now a stale and dusty remnant of another age. There is a fireplace along the north wall, a gun rack resting just above it. A large wooden cabinet stands tall just a few feet to the right of the fireplace. A deer mount hangs on the east wall, staring into the room with faux eyes. There is a sofa in the center of the room facing the fireplace; a painting hangs on the wall behind it.

You can climb the stairs to the second floor, travel South into the hallway, or enter the hidden room to the North.

