Upstairs Hallway East
The wood floors are warped and buckled from exposure to the elements. The paint has peeled away from the walls, and parts of the ceiling have fallen in from water damage. You notice that a trail of fresh blood comes from down the hall and stops at a door directly in front of you to the North.

The hallway continues West, and there is a door next to you to the East.

