Bedroom
You enter the bedroom and follow the trail of blood to a darkened corner. When you look up, you are startled to find a pair of milky white eyes watching your every move from the darkness. You stand still, shining your flashlight at the Lurking Shadow, but somehow its beam cannot penetrate it. The shadow speaks to you in a chillingly gurgled voice. "Find... her."

The decrepit bedroom has a dresser and a bed. You can exit South, the way you came.

> use skull on lurking shadow

> use skull on lurking shadow
The creature's milky white eyes follow you across the room as you place the Skull on the floor near the impenetrable shadow. After a few tense moments, a gangly misshapen hand reaches out, grabbing the skull and pulling it into the darkness. A haunting cry fills the room as an obscure figure emerges from the shadow. Standing in front of you is a creature so hideous that the mere sight of it leaves you disoriented and feeling faint. A wildly animated and fleshy juxtaposition of man and deer howls as it clutches the skull.

As you watch, frozen in terror, it runs on all fours toward the window, then jumps through the glass. You run to the window and find that the creature has vanished through the tall grass, back into the forest in which it came.

Turning your gaze back into the room, you see that your bloodied arrow lay on the floor.

(You unlocked an Achievement.)

